1

00:00:02,490  -->  00:00:08,384
You now have seen how a sampling distribution provides how a statistic varies.

2

00:00:08,384  -->  00:00:12,309
As we saw, the proportions change with different samples of students.

3

00:00:12,310  -->  00:00:16,914
However, we might also look at the distribution of other statistics,

4

00:00:16,914  -->  00:00:20,169
like how the sample standard deviation, the variance,

5

00:00:20,170  -->  00:00:25,570
difference in mean or any other statistic varies from one sample to the next.

6

00:00:25,570  -->  00:00:29,335
Notice, we are not looking at the distribution parameters.

7

00:00:29,335  -->  00:00:31,394
As you saw in the first example,

8

00:00:31,394  -->  00:00:36,485
the parameter that is a numeric summary of a population is a fixed value,

9

00:00:36,485  -->  00:00:38,570
so these values do not change.

10

00:00:38,570  -->  00:00:43,719
However, statistics will change based on a sample you select from the population.

11

00:00:43,719  -->  00:00:46,750
So what are the common traits of sampling distributions??
